{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm here to give you"},{"time":2000,"text":"your recommended dietary allowance"},{"time":4000,"text":"of poetry."},{"time":6000,"text":"And the way I'm going to do that"},{"time":8000,"text":"is present to you"},{"time":10000,"text":"five animations"},{"time":12000,"text":"of five of my poems."},{"time":14000,"text":"And let me just tell you a little bit of how that came about."},{"time":16000,"text":"Because the mixing of those two media"},{"time":18000,"text":"is a sort of unnatural or unnecessary act."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21000,"text":"But when I was United States Poet Laureate --"},{"time":25000,"text":"and I love saying that."},{"time":27000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":29000,"text":"It's a great way to start sentences."},{"time":32000,"text":"When I was him back then,"},{"time":35000,"text":"I was approached by J. Walter Thompson, the ad company,"},{"time":38000,"text":"and they were hired"},{"time":40000,"text":"sort of by the Sundance Channel."},{"time":42000,"text":"And the idea was to have me record some of my poems"},{"time":44000,"text":"and then they would find animators"},{"time":46000,"text":"to animate them."},{"time":48000,"text":"And I was initially resistant,"},{"time":50000,"text":"because I always think"},{"time":52000,"text":"poetry can stand alone by itself."},{"time":54000,"text":"Attempts to put my poems to music"},{"time":57000,"text":"have had disastrous results,"},{"time":59000,"text":"in all cases."},{"time":62000,"text":"And the poem, if it's written with the ear,"},{"time":65000,"text":"already has been set to its own verbal music"},{"time":68000,"text":"as it was composed."},{"time":70000,"text":"And surely, if you're reading a poem"},{"time":72000,"text":"that mentions a cow,"},{"time":74000,"text":"you don't need on the facing page"},{"time":76000,"text":"a drawing of a cow."},{"time":78000,"text":"I mean, let's let the reader do a little work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81000,"text":"But I relented because it seemed like an interesting possibility,"},{"time":84000,"text":"and also I'm like a total cartoon junkie"},{"time":87000,"text":"since childhood."},{"time":90000,"text":"I think more influential"},{"time":92000,"text":"than Emily Dickinson or Coleridge or Wordsworth"},{"time":95000,"text":"on my imagination"},{"time":97000,"text":"were Warner Brothers, Merrie Melodies"},{"time":99000,"text":"and Loony Tunes cartoons."},{"time":102000,"text":"Bugs Bunny is my muse."},{"time":106000,"text":"And this way poetry could find its way onto television of all places."},{"time":110000,"text":"And I'm pretty much all for poetry in public places --"},{"time":113000,"text":"poetry on buses, poetry on subways,"},{"time":116000,"text":"on billboards, on cereal boxes."},{"time":120000,"text":"When I was Poet Laureate, there I go again --"},{"time":124000,"text":"I can't help it, it's true --"},{"time":127000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":130000,"text":"I created a poetry channel on Delta Airlines"},{"time":133000,"text":"that lasted for a couple of years."},{"time":135000,"text":"So you could tune into poetry as you were flying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138000,"text":"And my sense is,"},{"time":140000,"text":"it's a good thing to get poetry off the shelves"},{"time":143000,"text":"and more into public life."},{"time":145000,"text":"Start a meeting with a poem. That would be an idea you might take with you."},{"time":148000,"text":"When you get a poem on a billboard or on the radio"},{"time":151000,"text":"or on a cereal box or whatever,"},{"time":153000,"text":"it happens to you so suddenly"},{"time":155000,"text":"that you don't have time"},{"time":157000,"text":"to deploy your anti-poetry deflector shields"},{"time":161000,"text":"that were installed in high school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166000,"text":"So let us start with the first one."},{"time":169000,"text":"It's a little poem called \"Budapest,\""},{"time":172000,"text":"and in it I reveal,"},{"time":174000,"text":"or pretend to reveal,"},{"time":176000,"text":"the secrets of the creative process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181000,"text":"(Video) Narration: \"Budapest.\""},{"time":183000,"text":"My pen moves along the page"},{"time":186000,"text":"like the snout of a strange animal"},{"time":189000,"text":"shaped like a human arm"},{"time":191000,"text":"and dressed in the sleeve"},{"time":193000,"text":"of a loose green sweater."},{"time":195000,"text":"I watch it sniffing the paper ceaselessly,"},{"time":198000,"text":"intent as any forager"},{"time":201000,"text":"that has nothing on its mind"},{"time":203000,"text":"but the grubs and insects"},{"time":206000,"text":"that will allow it to live another day."},{"time":209000,"text":"It wants only to be here tomorrow,"},{"time":212000,"text":"dressed perhaps"},{"time":214000,"text":"in the sleeve of a plaid shirt,"},{"time":216000,"text":"nose pressed against the page,"},{"time":218000,"text":"writing a few more dutiful lines"},{"time":222000,"text":"while I gaze out the window"},{"time":224000,"text":"and imagine Budapest"},{"time":226000,"text":"or some other city"},{"time":228000,"text":"where I have never been."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232000,"text":"BC: So that makes it seem a little easier."},{"time":235000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":237000,"text":"Writing is not actually as easy as that for me."},{"time":241000,"text":"But I like to pretend that it comes with ease."},{"time":246000,"text":"One of my students came up after class, an introductory class,"},{"time":249000,"text":"and she said, \"You know, poetry is harder than writing,\""},{"time":254000,"text":"which I found both erroneous and profound."},{"time":257000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":260000,"text":"So I like to at least pretend it just flows out."},{"time":263000,"text":"A friend of mine has a slogan; he's another poet."},{"time":266000,"text":"He says that, \"If at first you don't succeed,"},{"time":269000,"text":"hide all evidence you ever tried.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":272000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":274000,"text":"The next poem is also rather short."},{"time":277000,"text":"Poetry just says a few things in different ways."},{"time":280000,"text":"And I think you could boil this poem down to saying,"},{"time":283000,"text":"\"Some days you eat the bear, other days the bear eats you.\""},{"time":286000,"text":"And it uses the imagery"},{"time":288000,"text":"of dollhouse furniture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290000,"text":"(Video) Narration: \"Some Days.\""},{"time":294000,"text":"Some days"},{"time":296000,"text":"I put the people in their places at the table,"},{"time":299000,"text":"bend their legs at the knees,"},{"time":301000,"text":"if they come with that feature,"},{"time":303000,"text":"and fix them into the tiny wooden chairs."},{"time":307000,"text":"All afternoon they face one another,"},{"time":310000,"text":"the man in the brown suit,"},{"time":312000,"text":"the woman in the blue dress --"},{"time":314000,"text":"perfectly motionless, perfectly behaved."},{"time":318000,"text":"But other days I am the one"},{"time":320000,"text":"who is lifted up by the ribs"},{"time":322000,"text":"then lowered into the dining room of a dollhouse"},{"time":326000,"text":"to sit with the others at the long table."},{"time":329000,"text":"Very funny."},{"time":331000,"text":"But how would you like it"},{"time":333000,"text":"if you never knew from one day to the next"},{"time":336000,"text":"if you were going to spend it"},{"time":338000,"text":"striding around like a vivid god,"},{"time":341000,"text":"your shoulders in the clouds,"},{"time":344000,"text":"or sitting down there"},{"time":346000,"text":"amidst the wallpaper"},{"time":348000,"text":"staring straight ahead"},{"time":350000,"text":"with your little plastic face?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":356000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":361000,"text":"BC: There's a horror movie in there somewhere."},{"time":364000,"text":"The next poem is called forgetfulness,"},{"time":366000,"text":"and it's really just a kind of poetic essay"},{"time":368000,"text":"on the subject of mental slippage."},{"time":372000,"text":"And the poem begins"},{"time":374000,"text":"with a certain species of forgetfulness"},{"time":377000,"text":"that someone called"},{"time":379000,"text":"literary amnesia,"},{"time":381000,"text":"in other words, forgetting the things that you have read."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388000,"text":"(Video) Narration: \"Forgetfulness.\""},{"time":390000,"text":"The name of the author is the first to go,"},{"time":393000,"text":"followed obediently"},{"time":395000,"text":"by the title, the plot,"},{"time":397000,"text":"the heartbreaking conclusion,"},{"time":399000,"text":"the entire novel,"},{"time":401000,"text":"which suddenly becomes one you have never read,"},{"time":404000,"text":"never even heard of."},{"time":406000,"text":"It is as if, one by one,"},{"time":408000,"text":"the memories you used to harbor"},{"time":411000,"text":"decided to retire to the southern hemisphere of the brain"},{"time":415000,"text":"to a little fishing village"},{"time":417000,"text":"where there are no phones."},{"time":419000,"text":"Long ago,"},{"time":421000,"text":"you kissed the names of the nine muses good-bye"},{"time":424000,"text":"and you watched the quadratic equation"},{"time":426000,"text":"pack its bag."},{"time":428000,"text":"And even now,"},{"time":430000,"text":"as you memorize the order of the planets,"},{"time":432000,"text":"something else is slipping away,"},{"time":434000,"text":"a state flower perhaps,"},{"time":436000,"text":"the address of an uncle,"},{"time":438000,"text":"the capital of Paraguay."},{"time":440000,"text":"Whatever it is"},{"time":442000,"text":"you are struggling to remember,"},{"time":444000,"text":"it is not poised on the tip of your tongue,"},{"time":447000,"text":"not even lurking"},{"time":449000,"text":"in some obscure corner"},{"time":451000,"text":"of your spleen."},{"time":453000,"text":"It has floated away"},{"time":455000,"text":"down a dark mythological river"},{"time":458000,"text":"whose name begins with an L"},{"time":461000,"text":"as far as you can recall,"},{"time":463000,"text":"well on your own way to oblivion"},{"time":466000,"text":"where you will join those"},{"time":468000,"text":"who have forgotten even how to swim"},{"time":470000,"text":"and how to ride a bicycle."},{"time":473000,"text":"No wonder you rise in the middle of the night"},{"time":476000,"text":"to look up the date of a famous battle"},{"time":479000,"text":"in a book on war."},{"time":481000,"text":"No wonder the Moon in the window"},{"time":483000,"text":"seems to have drifted out of a love poem"},{"time":486000,"text":"that you used to know by heart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":500000,"text":"BC: The next poem is called \"The Country\""},{"time":502000,"text":"and it's based on,"},{"time":504000,"text":"when I was in college"},{"time":506000,"text":"I met a classmate who remains to be a friend of mine."},{"time":509000,"text":"He lived, and still does, in rural Vermont."},{"time":511000,"text":"I lived in New York City."},{"time":513000,"text":"And we would visit each other."},{"time":515000,"text":"And when I would go up to the country,"},{"time":517000,"text":"he would teach me things like deer hunting,"},{"time":520000,"text":"which meant getting lost with a gun basically --"},{"time":523000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":525000,"text":"and trout fishing and stuff like that."},{"time":527000,"text":"And then he'd come down to New York City"},{"time":529000,"text":"and I'd teach him what I knew,"},{"time":531000,"text":"which was largely smoking and drinking."},{"time":533000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":535000,"text":"And in that way we traded lore with each other."},{"time":538000,"text":"The poem that's coming up"},{"time":540000,"text":"is based on him trying to tell me a little something"},{"time":543000,"text":"about a domestic point of etiquette"},{"time":545000,"text":"in country living"},{"time":547000,"text":"that I had a very hard time, at first, processing."},{"time":549000,"text":"It's called \"The Country.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":551000,"text":"(Video) Narration: \"The Country.\""},{"time":554000,"text":"I wondered about you"},{"time":556000,"text":"when you told me never to leave"},{"time":558000,"text":"a box of wooden strike-anywhere matches"},{"time":561000,"text":"just lying around the house,"},{"time":564000,"text":"because the mice might get into them"},{"time":566000,"text":"and start a fire."},{"time":568000,"text":"But your face was absolutely straight"},{"time":571000,"text":"when you twisted the lid down"},{"time":573000,"text":"on the round tin"},{"time":575000,"text":"where the matches, you said, are always stowed."},{"time":578000,"text":"Who could sleep that night?"},{"time":580000,"text":"Who could whisk away the thought"},{"time":582000,"text":"of the one unlikely mouse"},{"time":585000,"text":"padding along a cold water pipe"},{"time":588000,"text":"behind the floral wallpaper,"},{"time":590000,"text":"gripping a single wooden match"},{"time":592000,"text":"between the needles of his teeth?"},{"time":595000,"text":"Who could not see him rounding a corner,"},{"time":598000,"text":"the blue tip scratching against rough-hewn beam,"},{"time":601000,"text":"the sudden flare"},{"time":603000,"text":"and the creature, for one bright, shining moment,"},{"time":607000,"text":"suddenly thrust ahead of his time --"},{"time":609000,"text":"now a fire-starter,"},{"time":611000,"text":"now a torch-bearer"},{"time":613000,"text":"in a forgotten ritual,"},{"time":615000,"text":"little brown druid"},{"time":617000,"text":"illuminating some ancient night?"},{"time":619000,"text":"And who could fail to notice,"},{"time":622000,"text":"lit up in the blazing insulation,"},{"time":624000,"text":"the tiny looks of wonderment"},{"time":626000,"text":"on the faces of his fellow mice --"},{"time":629000,"text":"one-time inhabitants"},{"time":631000,"text":"of what once was your house in the country?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":635000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":638000,"text":"BC: Thank you."},{"time":640000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":642000,"text":"Thank you. And the last poem is called \"The Dead.\""},{"time":645000,"text":"I wrote this after a friend's funeral,"},{"time":647000,"text":"but not so much about the friend as something the eulogist kept saying,"},{"time":649000,"text":"as all eulogists tend to do,"},{"time":651000,"text":"which is how happy the deceased would be"},{"time":654000,"text":"to look down and see all of us assembled."},{"time":656000,"text":"And that to me was a bad start to the afterlife,"},{"time":659000,"text":"having to witness your own funeral and feel gratified."},{"time":662000,"text":"So the little poem is called \"The Dead.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":666000,"text":"(Video) Narration: \"The Dead.\""},{"time":668000,"text":"The dead are always looking down on us,"},{"time":671000,"text":"they say."},{"time":673000,"text":"While we are putting on our shoes or making a sandwich,"},{"time":676000,"text":"they are looking down"},{"time":678000,"text":"through the glass-bottom boats of heaven"},{"time":681000,"text":"as they row themselves slowly"},{"time":683000,"text":"through eternity."},{"time":685000,"text":"They watch the tops of our heads"},{"time":687000,"text":"moving below on Earth."},{"time":689000,"text":"And when we lie down"},{"time":691000,"text":"in a field or on a couch,"},{"time":693000,"text":"drugged perhaps"},{"time":695000,"text":"by the hum of a warm afternoon,"},{"time":698000,"text":"they think we are looking back at them,"},{"time":701000,"text":"which makes them lift their oars"},{"time":703000,"text":"and fall silent"},{"time":705000,"text":"and wait like parents"},{"time":708000,"text":"for us to close our eyes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":720000,"text":"BC: I'm not sure if other poems will be animated."},{"time":722000,"text":"It took a long time --"},{"time":724000,"text":"I mean, it's rather uncommon to have this marriage --"},{"time":727000,"text":"a long time to put those two together."},{"time":729000,"text":"But then again, it took us a long time"},{"time":731000,"text":"to put the wheel and the suitcase together."},{"time":733000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":736000,"text":"I mean, we had the wheel for some time."},{"time":739000,"text":"And schlepping is an ancient and honorable art."}]},{"cues":[{"time":742000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":745000,"text":"I just have time"},{"time":747000,"text":"to read a more recent poem to you."},{"time":750000,"text":"If it has a subject,"},{"time":753000,"text":"the subject is adolescence."},{"time":755000,"text":"And it's addressed to a certain person."},{"time":757000,"text":"It's called \"To My Favorite 17-Year-Old High School Girl.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":763000,"text":"\"Do you realize that if you had started building the Parthenon"},{"time":766000,"text":"on the day you were born,"},{"time":768000,"text":"you would be all done in only one more year?"},{"time":771000,"text":"Of course, you couldn't have done that all alone."},{"time":773000,"text":"So never mind;"},{"time":775000,"text":"you're fine just being yourself."},{"time":777000,"text":"You're loved for just being you."},{"time":780000,"text":"But did you know that at your age"},{"time":782000,"text":"Judy Garland was pulling down 150,000 dollars a picture,"},{"time":787000,"text":"Joan of Arc was leading the French army to victory"},{"time":791000,"text":"and Blaise Pascal had cleaned up his room --"},{"time":794000,"text":"no wait, I mean he had invented the calculator?"},{"time":798000,"text":"Of course, there will be time for all that"},{"time":800000,"text":"later in your life,"},{"time":802000,"text":"after you come out of your room"},{"time":804000,"text":"and begin to blossom,"},{"time":806000,"text":"or at least pick up all your socks."},{"time":810000,"text":"For some reason I keep remembering"},{"time":812000,"text":"that Lady Jane Grey was queen of England"},{"time":814000,"text":"when she was only 15."},{"time":817000,"text":"But then she was beheaded, so never mind her as a role model."},{"time":820000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":823000,"text":"A few centuries later,"},{"time":825000,"text":"when he was your age,"},{"time":827000,"text":"Franz Schubert was doing the dishes for his family,"},{"time":831000,"text":"but that did not keep him"},{"time":833000,"text":"from composing two symphonies, four operas"},{"time":836000,"text":"and two complete masses as a youngster."},{"time":839000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":841000,"text":"But of course, that was in Austria"},{"time":843000,"text":"at the height of Romantic lyricism,"},{"time":846000,"text":"not here in the suburbs of Cleveland."},{"time":848000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":850000,"text":"Frankly, who cares"},{"time":852000,"text":"if Annie Oakley was a crack shot at 15"},{"time":855000,"text":"or if Maria Callas debuted as Tosca at 17?"},{"time":859000,"text":"We think you're special just being you --"},{"time":862000,"text":"playing with your food and staring into space."},{"time":865000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":868000,"text":"By the way,"},{"time":870000,"text":"I lied about Schubert doing the dishes,"},{"time":873000,"text":"but that doesn't mean he never helped out around the house.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":876000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":878000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":880000,"text":"Thank you. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":883000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":888000,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":890000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}